Experiment 17: 

Write a shell program to Calculate the gross salary of the employee where his DA is 40%   of basic salary and HRA is 20% of basic salary. Get basic salary as user input. # salary.sh
(Hint: Gross Salary = Basic Salary + DA + HRA  &   DA = 40% of Basic, HRA = 20% of Basic)

salary.sh
#!/bin/bash
read -p "Enter basic salary: " basic
da=$((basic*40/100))
hra=$((basic*20/100))
gross=$((basic+da+hra))
echo "Basic Salary = $basic"
echo "DA = $da"
echo "HRA = $hra"
echo "Gross Salary = $gross"

